{
  "stem": "10406.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My name is Leon Ginsburg-- G-I-N-S-B-U-R-G.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In Europe it was spelt with a Z, G-I-N-Z-B-U-R-G.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "During the war when I lived as a Catholic, my name was Stanislaw-- that's S-T-A-N-I-S-L-A-W-- Kwiatkowski.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that's a difficult one.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "K-W-I-A-T-K-O-W-S-K-I.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my birthdate is 6/12/1932.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I'm now 63.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was born in Poland in the-- an area called Volhynia.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it's like part of the Ukraine.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now it's an independent Ukrainian state.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the name of the town was Maciejow.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That's M-A-C-I-E-J-O-W.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Ukrainians now renamed it Lukov, L-U-K-O-V.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that was Poland up to 1939.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When the Germans invaded Poland, there was a pact between Hitler and Stalin where Russia was going to get the eastern part of Poland, which is the Ukraine.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So this area fell under the Russian occupation in 1939 until 1941.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Our town was a-- it was an Orthodox Jewish town.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I would say 60% or 70% of the population was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were surrounded by villages which were mostly Ukrainian and perhaps some Polish Catholic colonies.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We lived in like almost the center of the town.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there were-- there were streets.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The-- the streets were-- were cobble stones.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we had sidewalks.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there were some areas that were residential, just homes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then in the center of the town you had the-- where the stores were.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the marketplace was near the stores.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And on a certain-- certain day of the week, all the farmers that wanted to do business in town would come down with horse and wagon and park in that market area.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they would be selling their products to people in town that wanted to buy them, from fruits, to milk, and butter, and grain, and trading horses and other livestock.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We lived in a house.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I lived with my mother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And her name was Pesel.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And my sister, who was the oldest, her name was Blimele, [?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Blime. ?] And a brother, Herschel [? or ?] [?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Zvi. ?]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And a grandmother, Bela, Bela Goldberg.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was a town.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was a little town--",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--actually.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Before the war, I was already went through Polish kindergarten and probably in first grade, started in first grade.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was like half a day.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the other half a day, we went for Hebrew studies.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was a-- it was a a Talmud Torah, which was a combination of yeshiva-- actually, it was more of a yeshiva than-- than a Hebrew school because there was already competition between the younger modern generation, who were embracing Zionism and who wanted to learn Hebrew, in fact use Hebrew as a speaking language instead of Yiddish, which was spoken in most homes.",
      "word_count": 64
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we would learn basically the religious aspect of Judaism there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I would say Orthodox was, in that town, as conservative Judaism was in this area.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Everybody was sort of Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Although there was already a difference between the older generation that still wore beards and [? payot ?] and some of the Hasidic garb.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The younger generation already dressed in a modern way with suits and ties and were-- and didn't have any [? payot ?] anymore and didn't wear beards.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My parents owned a store that sold material for suits, and coats, and dresses, like a garment type of business.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my mother-- my mother worked in the store.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My brother and sister went to school, yes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, on that market day, which I believe was-- it was either Wednesday or Thursday, it would get very crowded, a lot of customers.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then my mother would ask us to come and help, like just to be in the store to make sure that-- you know, cause the shelves were open, people don't take things and walk out.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It-- I would say the center of the town and going outside towards the suburbs a little bit was mostly Jewish.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then starting from there, the farms would start already.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So it would be people that live in town but actually have land outside of the city and-- but they would have their livestock in-- in-- in the-- in the [?",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "CLO-- ?] in that area, in the barns.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So that would start already being non-Jewish.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that would be mostly Ukrainian.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because that area of Poland was-- was considered the Ukraine.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I would say 80% of the population was Ukrainian Orthodox-- Russian or Ukrainian Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And about 10% of the population was Polish Catholic.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then 10% of the overall population was 10% Jewish.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But in this particular town, probably 60% to 70% of the population was Jewish because all the crafts were concentrated there and the stores were concentrated in town.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
